    "body": "#### vim-patch:9.2.0470: No way to hook into put commands\r\n\r\nProblem:  No way to hook into put commands\r\n          (yochem)\r\nSolution: Introduce TextPutPre and TextPutPost autocommands\r\n          (Foxe Chen).\r\n\r\ncloses: vim/vim#20144\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/commit/e0781bd5bfd1acc2c4d5d01ec60fecafc99ee3e2\r\n\r\nCo-authored-by: Foxe Chen <chen.foxe@gmail.com>\r\n\r\n\r\n#### vim-patch:9.2.0473: Pasting \". register without autocommands breaks TextPut*\r\n\r\nProblem:  Pasting \". register without TextPut* autocommands breaks\r\n          subsequent TextPut* autocommands (after 9.2.0470).\r\nSolution: Only decrement add_last_insert if it has been incremented\r\n          (zeertzjq).\r\n\r\ncloses: vim/vim#20192\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/commit/a70b7a85afad9dc8eeae2a97142dc744cf3205e6\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "great to see this! closes https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/15136 ?\r\n\r\nsome notes:\r\n\r\n- should the tests explicitly cover `:put` (and maybe `:put =...` is interesting?)\r\n- do we need tests for these (and a tracking issue if they don't work):\r\n    - `nvim_put()`\r\n    - `nvim_paste()`\r\n    - `nvim_buf_set_text()`\r\n    - `nvim_buf_set_lines()`",
            "created_at": "2026-05-11T20:04:48Z",
